<item>
            <title>[LU-8483] sanity.sh aborts after test 117 due to get_param error</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8483</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running sanity.sh on 1 client, 1 MDT, and 1 OST, I consistently find it fails just after test 117 due to a get_params error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; SKIP: sanity test_117 skipping ALWAYS excluded test 117
error: get_param: param_path &apos;osc/lustrewt-OST*-osc-*/resend_count&apos;: No such file or directory
error: set_param: param_path &apos;osc/lustrewt-OST*-osc-*/resend_count&apos;: No such file or directory
sanity.sh returned 0
Finished at Sun Aug  7 12:05:37 PDT 2016 in 2657s
./auster: completed with rc 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even if test 117 is excluded (as above), it still aborts.  It tells me that auster completed with rc of 0, but that is not true.  A test earlier did fail, and there are more tests which did not get run because of this abort.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="38649">LU-8483</key>
